Taurian Manganese plans $150 Million Zambia Plant, Reuters Says

-- B y   L a r s   P a u l s s o n
-- 
2011-04-17T11:37:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-17/taurian-manganese-plans-150-million-zambia-plant-reuters-says.html
Taurian Manganese Ltd. plans to
build a $150 million manganese plant in central Zambia, Reuters
said today, citing Imran Merchant, a company official.  Construction of the plant, with an annual capacity of
720,000 tons and employ 700 workers was expected to start in
June, Reuters said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lars Paulsson in London at 
 lpaulsson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
 sev@bloomberg.net  